#
# Hardcoded SwiftUI `Text("Foo")` literal count — Humble UI G4 ratchet.
#
# Per ADR-021/043 + ADR-038, every user-visible string lives in
# `locales/*.json` and is read via `LocalizationService.shared.t("foo.key")`.
# A `Text("Foo")` literal bypasses i18n.
#
# Scope: `Vauchi/Views/`, `Vauchi/CoreUI/`, and `Vauchi/VauchiApp.swift`.
# Scanned by `just lint macos` via `scripts/scripts/check-text-literal-count.sh`.
#
# G4 closed in Phase 1c (macos!201): the only 2 prior matches lived in
# `PlaceholderContentView`'s `#if !canImport(VauchiPlatform)` dev fallback
# and moved to `let` constants. The baseline is 0 and any reintroduction
# must be justified — typically via locale keys, occasionally via constants
# in pre-binding fallback code.

0
